Q: Unable to redirect JavaScript URL via browser extension from certain website due to CSP A: <p>For <code>targetB</code>, instead of redirecting the script request, inject your replacement script via <code>content_scripts</code> or <code>chrome.scripting.executeScript</code>. That bypasses CSP entirely because extension scripts are privileged and not subject to site CSP.</p>
<p><code>manifest.json</code> code:</p>
<pre class="lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>{
  &quot;manifest_version&quot;: 3,
  &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Inject Script Example&quot;,
  &quot;version&quot;: &quot;1.0&quot;,
  &quot;permissions&quot;: [
    &quot;scripting&quot;,
    &quot;tabs&quot;
  ],
  &quot;host_permissions&quot;: [
    &quot;*://targetB.org/*&quot;
  ],
  &quot;background&quot;: {
    &quot;service_worker&quot;: &quot;background.js&quot;
  }
}
</code></pre>
<p><code>background.js</code> code:</p>
<pre class="lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>chrome.webNavigation.onCompleted.addListener((details) =&gt; {
  if (details.url.includes(&quot;targetB.org&quot;)) {
    chrome.scripting.executeScript({
      target: { tabId: details.tabId },
      files: [&quot;targetB/target.js&quot;]
    });
  }
});
</code></pre>
<p><code>target.js</code> code:</p>
<pre class="lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>console.log(&quot;Injected replacement.&quot;);
</code></pre>

Q: Recommended workaround for circular import issue? A: <p>Here's what I did. I put the three as class objects attributes instead. But I'm still receiving the circular import issue:</p>
<pre><code>import discord
from game.rock_paper_scissors.views.rps_views import (
        RpsMainMenuView,
        RpsMovesView
    )

from game.rock_paper_scissors.views.how_to_play_views import (
        HowToPlayView
    )


class RpsNavigate(discord.ui.View):

    rps_main_menu_view = RpsMainMenuView()
    how_to_play_view = HowToPlayView()
    rps_moves_view = RpsMovesView()

    def __init__(self):
        self = self



    def determine_view(self, view_choice):
        self.view_choice = view_choice
        print(f&quot;[RPS Navigate] Determining views to be passed: {self.view_choice}&quot;)



        if self.view_choice == &quot;RPS&quot;:
            return self.rps_main_menu_view
        elif self.view_choice == &quot;HTP&quot;:
            return self.how_to_play_view
        elif self.view_choice == &quot;RMV&quot;:
            return self.rps_moves_view
        else:
            return self.rps_main_menu_view

</code></pre>
<p>I double checked as well that <code>rps.py</code> (added in the post), <code>how_to_play_views.py</code>, and <code>rps_views.py</code> don't call each other and only calls rps_navigate.py.</p>
<p>Also, I did consider putting it in one python file instead (the <code>how_to_play_views.py</code>'s code will be in <code>rps_views.py</code>) but though I am a beginner, I do want to challenge myself even as simple as this and as early as now, ingrain some best practices.</p>
